# API Architecture

## Router mounting

- `app.ts` sets up global middleware, health check, and error handling only.
- `server.ts` is the router filter: mount all domain routers here (e.g. `app.use("/users", usersRouter)`).
- Do not mount domain routers in `app.ts`.

## Route organization

- Keep all routes for a domain in its router file (e.g. auth + CRUD routes live in `users-router.ts`).
- Routers should stay thin: validate input, call model/lib functions, return responses.

## Data access

- Database queries live in `src/models/<domain>/<domain>-queries.ts` (reads/writes for that model).
- Example: `src/models/users/user-queries.ts` for `createUser`, `getUsers`, `getUserById`.

## Auth logic

- Auth utilities live in `src/lib/auth/`:
  - `password.ts` — hash and compare passwords
  - `jwt.ts` — sign and verify tokens
  - `login.ts` — login flow (returns token)
  - `logout.ts` — revoke token/session
  - `session.ts` — session persistence helpers
- Middleware in `src/middleware/` handles request-level auth checks only.
